description:
Replace k_panic() calls in lichen_l2_reinit_after_abort().

Locations: lines 1626, 1638

Case 1 (line 1626): Called while module is running
Current:
  if (lichen_lora_l2_is_running()) {
      LOG_ERR("SECURITY: ... refusing to corrupt mutex");
      k_panic();
  }

Target:
  if (lichen_lora_l2_is_running()) {
      LOG_ERR("lichen_l2: reinit_after_abort called while running (caller bug)");
      return;  // Just don't reinit - better than corrupting
  }

Case 2 (line 1638): k_mutex_init failed
Current:
  if (ret != 0) {
      LOG_ERR("rx_mutex reinit failed");
      k_panic();
  }

Target: k_mutex_init cannot fail in Zephyr kernel mode (only in userspace).
Remove the check or leave LOG_ERR but don't panic. If it ever does fail,
returning leaves us in broken state, but watchdog will reset.
